07/07/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- The military drill "Albania Express 06", which includes the participation of 150 British soldiers, is under way at the Zallherr military facility. On Thursday (6 July), Defence Minister Fatmir Mediu, Chief of General Staff Pelumb Qazimi and British Ambassador to Tirana Richard Jones inspected the exercise. The soldiers demonstrated the use of anti-tank rockets and 81mm missiles, as well as camouflage techniques. This is the first in a series of training sessions organised by the British Army's "Outreach Programme 06". (Albanian News - 07/07/06) 
